Hackers warn Sony not to "make additional trouble"
CNN says it obtained the email from a Sony Pictures source. The email was sent to several Sony executives, and was formatted similarly to other messages from the hackers. "We want you never let the movie released, distributed or leaked in any form of, for instance, DVD or piracy," the hackers reportedly wrote. "And we want everything related to the movie, including its trailers, as well as its full version down from any website hosting them immediately." The hackers warned that they still had "private and sensitive data" that they hadn't yet released. They warned that this data wouldn't be released "unless you make additional trouble." On FridayÂ   it believed North Korea was responsible for the Sony attacks. Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 